Anti-Semitic attacks surged worldwide by 38 per cent last year , with the highest number of incidents occurring in France , an annual study .
The report said 766 violent anti-Semitic acts were carried out around the world last year .
Arson , vandalism and direct threats against Jews , synagogues and other Jewish institutions were included in the figure , making 2014 the worst year for such attacks since 2009 .
In France , the number 141 attacks rose to 164 in 2014 compared with 141 in 2014 .